            "answer_text": "All Egyptians are and were Africans because Egypt is in Africa. But there is no \u201cAfrican\u201d look, Africa was and is a very diverse continent. If you want to speak about Negroid people, ancient Egyptians were not Negroid people based on genetic researches and anthropologic features of mummies. Actually, modern Egyptians have a little bit more Sub-Saharan ancestry because of the slave trade, than ancient Egyptians had. Ancient Egyptians were closely related to the Caucasoid population of Levant: \u201cBoth types of genomic material showed that ancient Egyptians shared little DNA with modern sub-Saharan Africans. Instead, their closest relatives were people living during the Neolithic and Bronze ages in an area known as the Levant. Strikingly, the mummies were more closely related to ancient Europeans and Anatolians than to modern Egyptians.\u201d Mummy DNA unravels ancient Egyptians\u2019 ancestry ",
